# Generated by `cargo run --bin story-map`. The tool renders with LF and the
# staleness check (`--check`) compares byte-for-byte, so these must stay LF in
# the working tree on every platform — otherwise core.autocrlf=true would check
# them out as CRLF and the check would spuriously report STALE.
docs/story-map.md   text eol=lf
docs/story-map.json text eol=lf
